		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper06</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>The Moldable Debugger: A Framework for Developing Domain-Specific Debuggers</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AndreiChiș.html">Andrei Chiș</a>, <a href="../profile/TudorGîrba.html">Tudor Gîrba</a>, <a href="../profile/OscarNierstrasz.html">Oscar Nierstrasz</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_6">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_6</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2014s/paper05.html"><em>Practical domain-specific debuggers using the Moldable Debugger framework</em></a> (SLE 2014 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It proposes a debugger framework intended as a reusable workbench for building domain-specific debuggers.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> It targets debugging of running systems, i.e., runtime inspection and interaction.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It supports domain-specific debugging concepts/views tailored to particular domains/languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The motivation is to improve the effectiveness of debugging by offering domain-appropriate interactions.
</li></ul></li></ul>
